There are two differences between them:

1. If you use the `&lt;p&gt;{{msg}}&lt;/p&gt;` to bind the data, you can add more content, such as:

    &lt;p&gt;Hi, {{msg}}!&lt;/p&gt;

2. The `&lt;p v-text=&quot;msg&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;` can avoid the bind flashing, that mean when you load the view, there will not appear `{{msg}}` like the first way. If you want to use `&lt;p&gt;Hi, {{msg}}!&lt;/p&gt;` way, you can add the `[v-cloak]` property:
```
